"title": "5809: compassion, human",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5809: compassion, human",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>An attitude of care and concern, grounded in pity and sympathy towards others.  Christian compassion towards others should reflect the compassion of God for his people.</p>\n<h2>Compassion is a vital requirement in Christian character</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:32\">EPH 4:32</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:12\">COL 3:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:3-2Cor1:5\">2CO 1:3–1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:8\">1PE 3:8</a></p>\n<h2>Compassion needs to be shown in actions</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:17\">1JN 3:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:6-Isa58:7\">ISA 58:6–58:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:42\">MAT 10:42</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:41\">MRK 9:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:35-Matt25:36\">MAT 25:35–25:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:35\">ACT 20:35</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of compassionate behaviour</h2>\n<h3>To the oppressed and needy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job29:12-Job29:17\">JOB 29:12–29:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:25\">JOB 30:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:31\">PRO 14:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:33-Luke10:35\">LUK 10:33–10:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:2\">ACT 28:2</a></p>\n<h3>To the bereaved</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:35\">GEN 37:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:1-Ruth2:20\">RUT 2:1–2:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam10:1-2Sam10:2\">2SA 10:1–10:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr7:22\">1CH 7:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:19\">JHN 11:19</a></p>\n<h3>To children</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:6\">EXO 2:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:26\">1KI 3:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:15\">ISA 49:15</a></p>\n<h3>To prisoners</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:15\">2CH 28:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:9\">2CH 30:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:33-Acts16:34\">ACT 16:33–16:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:3\">HEB 13:3</a></p>\n<h3>To forgiven sinners</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor2:7-2Cor2:8\">2CO 2:7–2:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:1\">GAL 6:1</a></p>\n<h3>To the sick</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:11-Job2:13\">JOB 2:11–2:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:13\">PSA 35:13</a></p>\n<h3>To the solitary</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:10-Eccl4:11\">ECC 4:10–4:11</a></p>\n<h3>To widows and orphans</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:9-Zech7:10\">ZEC 7:9–7:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:27\">JAS 1:27</a></p>\n<h3>To Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:14\">PSA 102:14</a></p>\n<h2>God inspires human compassion</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:9\">DAN 1:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:21\">EXO 3:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:46\">PSA 106:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer42:12\">JER 42:12</a></p>\n<h2>God rewards compassion</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:21\">PRO 14:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps112:4-Ps112:5\">PSA 112:4–112:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:17\">PRO 19:17</a></p>\n<h2>Lack of compassion</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:6\">2SA 12:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:20\">PSA 69:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:16\">PSA 109:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:5\">EZK 16:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:11\">AMO 1:11</a></p>\n<h2>Limits of human compassion</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:53-Deut28:57\">DEU 28:53–28:57</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:18\">ISA 13:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer21:7\">JER 21:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam4:10\">LAM 4:10</a></p>",
